verbose_text: XREF_BIBR Autosomal-recessive spinocerebellar ataxia 1 (AOA2 or SCAR1 [MIM 606002]), a progressive ataxia, XREF_BIBR occurring later than AOA1, is characterized by increased alpha-fetoprotein levels and is caused by mutations in SETX (senataxin).
